HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 192
BY REPRESENTATIVE SPELL
COMMENDATIONS: Commends the American College of Obstetricians and
Gynecologists on the occasion of its seventy-fifth anniversary
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend the American College of Obstetricians and Gynecologists on the occasion of
3 its seventy-fifth anniversary.
4 WHEREAS, the American College of Obstetricians and Gynecologists (ACOG) was
5 founded in 1951, and for seventy-five years, has advanced the health and well-being of
6 patients through excellence in clinical practice, education, advocacy, and research; and
7 WHEREAS, ACOG represents more than sixty-two thousand health care
8 professionals nationwide, including more than seven hundred members in Louisiana who
9 provide essential obstetric and gynecologic care to patients across the state; and
10 WHEREAS, ACOG and its members in Louisiana have championed initiatives to
11 improve maternal health, protect the patient-physician relationship, and ensure access to
12 health care for all individuals; and
13 WHEREAS, ACOG works to create a stronger, more sustainable practice
14 environment for obstetrician-gynecologists and their patients; and
15 WHEREAS, the seventy-fifth anniversary of ACOG offers an opportunity to
16 recognize its historic contributions and reaffirm its commitment to advancing the health of
17 patients in Louisiana.
18 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
19 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby commend the American College of Obstetricians and
20 Gynecologists on the occasion of its seventy-fifth anniversary; does hereby recognize the
